oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Fairfield Trolley
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Fairfield Trolley before it was glassed in. The trolley was located in the Glendale Park area. Edgar Yound Clarke is standing next the trolley and Mr. Judd, who was the conductor, is standing inside of the trolley. Women are seated in the trolley.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Street railroads; Passengers
